title: 15 MIN FULL BODY STRETCH - Improve Mobility and Flexibility
description:
Join ​⁠@MarieSteffen and I for a 15 min full body smooth stretch routine! This will help you recover faster and increase your range of motion. All you need is flat space, use a mat for extra comfort!

Just remember, mobility is key for many HIIT and Strength exercises, so make sure to include regular stretching in your week and stay consistent with it!

♡📱 My workout APP has a new design and lots of exclusive workouts, sign up to my Grow with Anna APP today: https://www.growwithanna.com/

▸ Level: All Levels
▸ Time: 15 Min
▸ Equipment: No Equipment
▸ Full Body Stretch 50 sec on, 10 sec rest

Please remember that we are all different and that you can make this your own workout ♡ Take a longer break when you need to.

comments: Hey Team ❤ I hope you enjoy this rest day routine, give back some self love to your body! I’m sure you’ll feel better after it 🤗 Anna x

taking care of my body is so important to me. i never used to exercise or practice mindfulness or ate food that actually made me feel good. and now it’s like a whole new perspective. i’m more grateful for everything and generally more at peace with myself. it’s easier to manage tasks. i’m sleeping better. it’s amazing.
I got my periods today and this was literally all i needed! I was not in the mood to do any high intensity ones and you posted this right on time >< thank you soo muchh anna 💖

When I read “Take Care of Your Body, It's Your Home,” I felt mixed emotions.  I don't know if it's sadness, a desire to cry, or a feeling of pity for what I do to myself every day.  In fact, eating disorders destroy a person's life and can even kill them.  Thank you for your work and thank you for your effort ❤❤❤

After suffering from an incomplete paralyzation with 17, I was in hospital for half a year, learning to walk again. Now it's been 3 ¾ years and right after getting out of hospital my physio started to use various Yoga stretches and exercises in our weekly appointments. Then I visited a yoga class in my gym once and been doing it since then. I was very flexible before the accident and I gained it all back, despite the metal and titan pieces holding my back and my feets together. So, I have to say thank you. Been watching your channel for a while and it helped me very much on my ongoing journey. It makes me proud to be able to follow along with most positions correctly when I once couldn't even move my legs. So please keep up the good work, it is worth it! 😁
